Description: Bowstring is a production studio.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Bowstring is a full-service production studio that travels the world to produce award-winning content for brands, agencies, and networks. At Bowstring Studios, our mission is to master the latest technologies and maintain artistic excellence as we create media that brings stories to life. Our team produces content that communicates powerful messages, elevates human experiences, engages audiences, and inspires action.  CEO Enrique Mendoza and President Sean Quinn started Bowstring Studios in 2001 with the mission to be great storytellers.Today, Enrique and Sean lead an integrated team of over 25 innovators that are driven by customized workflows and rare ingenuity. Our team of artists and technologists share a common goal to constantly evolve storytelling and produce the highest-quality content for our partners and clients.  THE STUDIO: Just outside of Philadelphia sits a quiet, spacious, and state-of-the-art production studio. Our Conshohocken shooting stage is the ideal space for video productions and photography shoots of all sizes. The full-service studio offers a 20′ x 9′ stage, 12′ clear space to the light grid, high-intensity studio lighting and green/white cyc wall (infinity backdrop) with a cove. There is plenty of on-site parking and load-in access is only 20 feet from the stage. With nearly 2000SF of total space, there is ample room for crew, talent, and clients, including enclosed makeup and green rooms, as well as full bathrooms and a catering-ready kitchen. The space also includes a lounge area where clients and talent can relax and view the production. The production studio rental fee includes electricity and basic grip equipment, with access to Bowstring’s extensive lighting, camera and grip catalogs always available as additional services. As a full-service production studio, Bowstring can also help with crew, editorial, graphics, post sound – ask us how we can be your partner in your next production.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment, Video
Founders: Enrique Mendoza, Sean Quinn, Varun Jain

Description: District Distillers Inc. is dedicated to the distillation of premium spirits within the booming craft distilling market.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: District Distillers Inc. is dedicated to the distillation of premium spirits within the booming craft distilling market. The company’s brand, Cotton & Reed, represents a portfolio of experimental spirits using natural ingredients and innovative distillation techniques. As consumers become increasingly focused on product origins, with movements like farm-to-table, Cotton & Reed is bringing this approach to the spirits world by distilling local, sometimes hand-foraged plants. BRAND: Cotton & Reed is named for our cofounders in the long tradition of eponymy in spirits. The name also calls to mind the verdant intersection of agriculture and nature at which our products sit. “Cotton” represents carefully cultivated plants like corn and wheat that form the basis of many of our spirits; wild-growing “reed” represents the more natural and unknown aspects of our products and marketing imagery. Our name simultaneously describes the origins of our company and our natural products as spirits consumers value origin stories and authenticity. MARKET: The craft spirits market is booming. Industry analysts expect producer revenue in the craft distillery market to grow at a 15-25% CAGR for the next 10-20 years. The craft distilling movement is still considered to be in 'early innings' as it begins to mirror craft beer’s growth trajectory. The growing preference for locally-produced products with a human story, combined with an exploding cocktail culture, have created a thirst for creative spirits.  ADVISERS: Our team is advised by spirits industry and startup veterans including: Jim Beam’s recently departed Global VP for Innovation; the team that created the Ogilvy Award-winning Makers Mark 'It Is What It Isn't' ad strategy; a venture capitalist with 30 years of experience, and a DC entrepreneur with extensive restaurant connections.

Description: EnzymatiX is a provider of cost-effective/efficient enzymes/enzyme systems for use in various industries.
Full Description: EnzymatiX is dedicated to producing cost-effective and efficient enzymes/enzyme systems for use in biofuels, paper and pulp industry, animal nutrition, starch and textile industries. We are involved in the discovery, molecular engineering, characterization and production of unique enzymes from fungus and other eukaryotic organisms found in nature. The promise of renewable energy is constantly evolving with the ever-increasing demand towards meeting the energy needs of the world. Dwindling oil reserves coupled with environmental concerns are the driving forces behind the need to look for alternative source of energy in nature. Lignocellulosic biomass is one such natural source of abundant energy on earth with a tremendous potential for bioconversion. In nature, many microorganisms including bacteria and fungi live on natural lignocellulosics; however the complexity of the lignocellulosic matrix makes it recalcitrant to complete degradation by microorganisms. A consortium of different enzymatic activities from multiple organisms is required to completely break down cell wall polymers to release the constituent sugars. Our patent-pending technology is dedicated to over produce novel enzymes or “cocktail” of enzymes to break down complex lignocelluloses into simple sugars without any harsh chemical pretreatment. We seek to harness the power of the microbes existing in nature to build a robust technological platform for production of biofuels and biobased products. Our enthusiastic, highly skilled and dynamic team can also partner with you to provide research tools for detection of enzymes using fluorescent labeled substrates
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Energy, Science and Engineering, Sustainability

Full Description: Data Description was founded in 1985 by Dr. Paul Velleman, a statistics professor at Cornell University. Data Description, Inc., of beautiful Ithaca, New York, has been developing quality educational and statistical software since 1986. Our flagship product is Data Desk, used for data mining, analysis and visualization by customers, academic and professional, around the globe. Our proprietary technology, MediaDX, is a content-rich multimedia instructional product used by educational institutions and corporations everywhere. Data Description, Inc., Ithaca, New York, is a software and development company dedicated to twin enterprises: data analysis and exploration and multimedia technology for training and education. We have a long record of successful innovation in both arenas and continue to pursue excellence and opportunities in each.  As award-winning pioneers in graphic display and statistical analysis, we create commercial software, custom applications, and integrated applications for data analysis and exploration. The idea driving these products, and what distinguishes them from competing developments, is that seeing is understanding. Anyone who needs to gain actionable insight from raw data will do that faster, more accurately, and more effectively if he or she can see the patterns in their data and explore the relationships among them. We are the leading developer of software tools for interactive data visualization and exploration, and an application development environment for customizing, extending and integrating these tools.  Using our proprietary MediaDX technology to serve customers in the corporate, government, and education markets, we develop interactive programs for computer-based learning. These content-rich productions deploy a full array of media, sound, video, narration, animation, and web access, to allow the user to learn, experience, and practice key concepts and important skills. They can be used to address any subject in any field, but are particularly well-suited for those disciplines where the practice of the discipline is performed on the computer, or can be simulated effectively on one.
